+# PublicMenu Review — 2026-03-29
+
+Scoped review of [CartView.jsx](/C:/Users/ASUS/Dev/Menu%20AI%20Cowork/menuapp-code-review/pages/PublicMenu/CartView.jsx) and [x.jsx](/C:/Users/ASUS/Dev/Menu%20AI%20Cowork/menuapp-code-review/pages/PublicMenu/x.jsx) against the numbered Fix 1-11 list in chain `publicmenu-260329-092204-e6b6`, with [README.md](/C:/Users/ASUS/Dev/Menu%20AI%20Cowork/menuapp-code-review/pages/PublicMenu/README.md) and [BUGS.md](/C:/Users/ASUS/Dev/Menu%20AI%20Cowork/menuapp-code-review/pages/PublicMenu/BUGS.md) read for page-local context only.
+
+## Findings
+1. [P1] CV-28 status buckets still render per-order rows instead of a flat grouped dish list — [CartView.jsx](/C:/Users/ASUS/Dev/Menu%20AI%20Cowork/menuapp-code-review/pages/PublicMenu/CartView.jsx#L519) still maps `orders` one by one, shows `getOrderTime(order)`, and toggles per-order chevrons via `expandedOrders`, so same-name dishes across orders are not merged within a bucket. FIX: replace `renderBucketOrders()` with bucket-level item aggregation by dish name, render one flat row per grouped dish, and remove `expandedOrders`, `getOrderSummary()`, and `getOrderTime()`.
+2. [P2] CV-29 separator lines are still present inside bucket content — [CartView.jsx](/C:/Users/ASUS/Dev/Menu%20AI%20Cowork/menuapp-code-review/pages/PublicMenu/CartView.jsx#L521) and [CartView.jsx](/C:/Users/ASUS/Dev/Menu%20AI%20Cowork/menuapp-code-review/pages/PublicMenu/CartView.jsx#L528) keep `border-t` on the bucket body and `border-b pb-2` on each rendered row, so the bucket content is still visually split by horizontal rules. FIX: remove row separators from status-bucket content when converting it to the flat grouped list.
+3. [P2] CV-30 drawer header still shows only the sum, not `N заказа · X ₸` — [CartView.jsx](/C:/Users/ASUS/Dev/Menu%20AI%20Cowork/menuapp-code-review/pages/PublicMenu/CartView.jsx#L665) still renders `{tr('cart.orders_sum', 'Заказов')}: {formatPrice(ordersSum)}` and never includes `todayMyOrders.length` or the required plural form. FIX: replace the block with `{count} {plural} · {formatPrice(ordersSum)}` using `todayMyOrders.length`.
+4. [P2] CV-31 table and guest are still split across two lines — [CartView.jsx](/C:/Users/ASUS/Dev/Menu%20AI%20Cowork/menuapp-code-review/pages/PublicMenu/CartView.jsx#L633) renders `tableLabel` on its own line and the guest control on a second line, so the requested single-line `Стол 11 · Гость 1 ›` layout is not implemented. FIX: combine table label and guest display/editor into one inline row with a `·` separator.
+5. [P2] CV-32 served bucket does not auto-collapse when the cart becomes non-empty — [CartView.jsx](/C:/Users/ASUS/Dev/Menu%20AI%20Cowork/menuapp-code-review/pages/PublicMenu/CartView.jsx#L93) initializes `served: false`, but there is no effect tied to cart state, so once the user expands `Подано` it stays open after new cart items are added. FIX: add a `useEffect` that forces only `expandedStatuses.served = false` when `cart.length > 0`.
+6. [P2] CV-33 split-order section was not removed — [CartView.jsx](/C:/Users/ASUS/Dev/Menu%20AI%20Cowork/menuapp-code-review/pages/PublicMenu/CartView.jsx#L90), [CartView.jsx](/C:/Users/ASUS/Dev/Menu%20AI%20Cowork/menuapp-code-review/pages/PublicMenu/CartView.jsx#L470), and [CartView.jsx](/C:/Users/ASUS/Dev/Menu%20AI%20Cowork/menuapp-code-review/pages/PublicMenu/CartView.jsx#L1008) still keep `splitExpanded`, `splitSummary`, and the full `Для кого заказ` radio UI. FIX: remove the split-order UI and the now-unused local state/computation so the cart always behaves as single-guest ordering.
+7. [P2] CV-34 cart items still show `price × 1` for single quantity — [CartView.jsx](/C:/Users/ASUS/Dev/Menu%20AI%20Cowork/menuapp-code-review/pages/PublicMenu/CartView.jsx#L981) always renders `{formatPrice(item.price)} × {item.quantity}`, so a single item still shows the redundant `× 1` line. FIX: render that subtitle only when `item.quantity > 1`.
+8. [P2] CV-35 `Новый заказ` spacing is still the old roomy layout — [CartView.jsx](/C:/Users/ASUS/Dev/Menu%20AI%20Cowork/menuapp-code-review/pages/PublicMenu/CartView.jsx#L967) and [CartView.jsx](/C:/Users/ASUS/Dev/Menu%20AI%20Cowork/menuapp-code-review/pages/PublicMenu/CartView.jsx#L968) still use `mb-4` and `p-4`, so the compact mobile spacing from the fix spec is not present. FIX: reduce the new-order card spacing to `mb-2` and `p-3` or equivalent tighter padding.
+9. [P2] PM-156 floating bell is still controlled only by `drawerMode !== 'cart'` — [x.jsx](/C:/Users/ASUS/Dev/Menu%20AI%20Cowork/menuapp-code-review/pages/PublicMenu/x.jsx#L3953) still renders the fixed bottom-left bell whenever `drawerMode` is not `'cart'`, which leaves the duplicate-bell bug exposed when drawer UI survives recovery but `drawerMode` resets. FIX: remove the floating bell block entirely or gate it with actual cart drawer visibility rather than `drawerMode` alone.
+10. [P2] PM-152 guest name clearing still depends on a fragile previous-ref comparison — [x.jsx](/C:/Users/ASUS/Dev/Menu%20AI%20Cowork/menuapp-code-review/pages/PublicMenu/x.jsx#L2465) only clears `menuapp_guest_name` when `prevTableRef.current` is truthy and differs from `tableCodeParam`, so after a fresh mount where the table code is initially empty and later hydrates, the first non-empty table code does not clear stale guest-name state. FIX: replace the current ref-based check with a table-code change effect that reliably clears state/localStorage when the table code changes between tables, while skipping the true initial load.
+11. [P1] PM-153 CartView still ignores `guestNameInput` as the guest-name fallback — [CartView.jsx](/C:/Users/ASUS/Dev/Menu%20AI%20Cowork/menuapp-code-review/pages/PublicMenu/CartView.jsx#L310) uses `currentGuest.name || getGuestDisplayName(currentGuest)` and otherwise falls back to generic `Гость`, so a saved localStorage-backed name is still ignored after recovery. FIX: use `guestNameInput` before `getGuestDisplayName(currentGuest)` and also in the no-`currentGuest` fallback path.
+
+## Summary
+Total: 11 findings (0 P0, 2 P1, 9 P2, 0 P3)
+
